-- Global Yatirim Ends Three-Day Slump on Bids for Energy Units
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-03-30T15:48:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-30/global-yatirim-rises-first-day-in-four-on-bids-for-energy-units.html
Global Yatirim Holding AS (GLYHO) , a
Turkish group with interests in financial services and energy,
advanced in Istanbul after saying it received preliminary bids
for minority stakes in its energy unit.  The shares added 3.4 percent to 1.21 liras at the close of
trading, ending a three-day decline. The increase brought the
stockâ€™s quarterly gain to 12 percent, making it the best quarter
since the first quarter of 2011.  Global received non-binding initial bids for stakes in
Global Enerji Hizmetleri & Isletmeciligi AS and its related
units and will start a due-diligence and bidding process for
selected investors, it said in a statement to the exchange
today. Raiffeisen Investment AG is advising, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
